<h2 id=3D"Final-Observations">Final Observations<a class=3D"anchor-link" hr=
ef=3D"file:///C:/Jottacloud/My%20Learning/MIT%20xPRO/Applied%20Data%20Scien=
ce/Elective%20Project/submission/High_Code_SVHN_Digit_Recognition.html#Fina=
l-Observations">=C2=B6</a></h2><h3 id=3D"1.-Overall-Model-Performance">1. O=
verall Model Performance<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"file:///C:/Jottacl=
oud/My%20Learning/MIT%20xPRO/Applied%20Data%20Science/Elective%20Project/su=
bmission/High_Code_SVHN_Digit_Recognition.html#1.-Overall-Model-Performance=
">=C2=B6</a></h3><ul>
<li><strong>High Accuracy</strong>: The second model generalizes well, as i=
ts accuracy is high above 85-90%.</li>
<li><strong>Balanced Learning:</strong> Precision and recall are nearly con=
sistent across all classes, this indicates stable learning.</li>
<li><strong>Balanced Generatization</strong> Compared to the first model, o=
verfitting has been reduced a lot, making the second model more reliable.</=
li>
<li><strong>Inference Speed</strong> The second model processes test data m=
ore efficiently, demonstrating optimized computation.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"2.-Class-Specific-Observations">2. Class-Specific Observations<a =
class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"file:///C:/Jottacloud/My%20Learning/MIT%20xPR=
O/Applied%20Data%20Science/Elective%20Project/submission/High_Code_SVHN_Dig=
it_Recognition.html#2.-Class-Specific-Observations">=C2=B6</a></h3><ul>
<li><strong>Best-performing classes:</strong> Classes 0, 2, 4, and 7 have h=
igh precision and recall, meaning they are correctly classified most of the=
 time.</li>
<li><strong>Challenging classes:</strong> Class 3 and 8 show lower recall s=
cores, meaning some actual samples of these classes are misclassified.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"3.-Confusion-Matrix-Intrepretation">3. Confusion Matrix Intrepret=
ation<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"file:///C:/Jottacloud/My%20Learning/M=
IT%20xPRO/Applied%20Data%20Science/Elective%20Project/submission/High_Code_=
SVHN_Digit_Recognition.html#3.-Confusion-Matrix-Intrepretation">=C2=B6</a><=
/h3><ul>
<li><strong>Main diagonal Values:</strong><ul>
<li>They represent the true positive rates for each class. These values sho=
w how many correct predictions were made for each class.</li>
<li>Most values are found concentrated along this diagonal, indicating that=
 most of predictions are correct.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Off-diagonal Values:</strong><ul>
<li>They represent the misclassifications. The goal is to have these values=
 be as low as possible.</li>
<li>I see that nearly all of the non-diagonal cells are being low values, i=
ndicating a low rate of misclassification.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
